.SH NAME
FileList \- FileList
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]FileList\f[B]\f[R] interface represents an object of this
type returned by the \f[CR]files\f[R] property of the HTML
\f[CR]<input>\f[R] element; this lets you access the list of files
selected with the \f[CR]<input type=\[dq]file\[dq]>\f[R] element.
It\[cq]s also used for a list of files dropped into web content when
using the drag and drop API; see the \f[CR]DataTransfer\f[R] object for
details on this usage.
.PP
All \f[CR]<input>\f[R] element nodes have a \f[CR]files\f[R] attribute
of type \f[CR]FileList\f[R] on them which allows access to the items in
this list.
For example, if the HTML includes the following file input:
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]input\f[R] id=\[dq]fileItem\[dq] type=\[dq]file\[dq] />
.EE
.PP
The following line of code fetches the first file in the node\[cq]s file
list as a \f[CR]File\f[R] object:
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] file = document.getElementById(\[dq]fileItem\[dq]).files[0];
.EE
.PP
This interface was an \c
.UR https://stackoverflow.com/questions/74630989/why-use-domstringlist-rather-than-an-array/74641156#74641156
attempt to create an unmodifiable list
.UE \c
\ and only continues to be supported to not break code that\[cq]s
already using it.
Modern APIs represent list structures using types based on JavaScript
arrays, thus making many array methods available, and at the same time
imposing additional semantics on their usage (such as making their items
read\-only).
.PP
These historical reasons do not mean that you as a developer should
avoid \f[CR]FileList\f[R].
You don\[cq]t create \f[CR]FileList\f[R] objects yourself, but you get
them from APIs such as \f[CR]HTMLInputElement.files\f[R], and these APIs
are not deprecated.
However, be careful of the semantic differences from a real array.
.SH INSTANCE PROPERTIES
.TP
\f[B]length\f[R] \f[I](read\-only)\f[R]
A read\-only value indicating the number of files in the list.
.SH INSTANCE METHODS
.TP
\f[B]item()\f[R]
Returns a \f[CR]File\f[R] object representing the file at the specified
index in the file list.
.SH EXAMPLE
.SS Logging filenames
In this example, we log the names of all the files selected by the user.
.SS HTML
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]input\f[R] id=\[dq]myfiles\[dq] multiple type=\[dq]file\[dq] />
<\f[B]pre\f[R] class=\[dq]output\[dq]>Selected files:</\f[B]pre\f[R]>
.EE
.SS CSS
.IP
.EX
\&.output {
  \f[B]overflow\f[R]: scroll;
  \f[B]margin\f[R]: 1rem 0;
  \f[B]height\f[R]: 200px;
}
.EE
.SS JavaScript
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] output = document.querySelector(\[dq].output\[dq]);
\f[B]const\f[R] fileInput = document.querySelector(\[dq]#myfiles\[dq]);

fileInput.addEventListener(\[dq]change\[dq], () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  \f[B]for\f[R] (\f[B]const\f[R] file \f[B]of\f[R] fileInput.files) {
    output.innerText += \[ga]\[rs]n${file.name}\[ga];
  }
});
.EE
